Buyer : Oh, 12MP… excellent pictures… no imperfections… that’s… that’s incredibly reassuring. Truly. But $320… it’s still pushing it. I’m starting to sweat, honestly. I’m picturing myself years from now, still using my old, cracked phone, wondering “what if?” It’s a terrifying thought. I’m desperate, you see. Desperate! I need this phone. But my budget… it’s so tight. I’m willing to stretch, I really am, but I’m so afraid of overextending myself and then regretting it even more. 

My counteroffer is 250. It’s the absolute maximum I can possibly spend. I’m sacrificing so much to even reach this number. Please, please, consider it. I promise I’ll take excellent care of the phone. I’ll cherish it. I’ll treat it like my own child! Just… please don’t make me live with the regret of letting this opportunity pass. I’m begging you. If it’s broken or very damaged, I will be so sad. So, so sad.



